properties.areaDesc: Delaware Bay waters south of East Point NJ to Slaughter Beach DE
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 10 at 2:50PM EST until January 12 at 12:00PM EST by NWS Mount Holly NJ
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 15 to 25 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and
rough waters possible.

* WHERE...Delaware Bay waters south of East Point NJ to
Slaughter Beach DE.

* WHEN...From Saturday evening through Sunday morning.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and seas.

NWSheadline: GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY EVENING THROUGH SUNDAY MORNING... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IS CANCELLED
